#31603
the Norstar Taiga~
   Ligonberry shrubs are scattered between the bases of the spruce trees in
this location where mosses and ferns haven't already claimed ground.  Their
berries are bright red and contrast heavily with the dark grey and green
evergreen leaves.  Birds can be heard flittering in between the needles of the
flora.  The air is quite chilly here bordering on the bitter cold that is sure
to be present farther north.  
~
