#31604
the Norstar Taiga~
   Tall black spruce trees tower up to 50 feet in this location and their
bluish-green needles form a spire at their peak.  Several different species of
ferns and moss battle for space to cover the ground.  The air is beginning to
chill here, with temperatures nearing bitter cold.  Sounds of wildlife are
fewer here with the occasional chirps emanating from small birds.  An
occasional piercing cry of an eagle overhead can be heard.  
~
