#31648
A Birch-plank Tree House~
   A primitive tree house built from surrounding birch trees.  There is a
comfortable looking bed in the north east corner.  A small window to the
north provides natural light.  The roof is thatch and covered in moss, which
hangs down from the ceiling in some places.  The floor is stable but creaks
loudly under any shift in weight.  A small wood burning stove is at the south
wall and is piped out the wall there.  
~
316 4 0 0 0 3
D5
~
~
0 0 31647
S
#31649
A Bone-filled Cave~
   Something horrible lives here, the stench is violently assaulting your
nostrils.  There are piles of bones and teeth everywhere, every step you take
sounds like two bucks wrestling.  The walls drip with moisture and bits of
meat and hair cake the lower spots.  Probably due to something obliterating
its prey without any proper table manners.  
~
316 4 0 0 0 3
D1
~
~
0 0 31641
S
#31650
the Norstar Taiga~
   As the larger flora become scarcerin this part of the Taiga, smaller brush
begins to take its place.  Mosses and ferns grow close to the ground where
moisture can be had.  Some grasses that vary from a thirsty gray appearance to
a parched light green.  These grasses sway in the occasional breeze that gives
indication to the sharply cold wind that was buffered by the trees further
south.  The temperature continues to drop here and is decidedly bitter cold.
~
