#31685
the Norstar Taiga~
   As the larger flora become scarcerin this part of the Taiga, smaller brush
begins to take its place.  Mosses and ferns grow close to the ground where
moisture can be had.  Some grasses that vary from a thirsty gray appearance to
a parched light green.  These grasses sway in the occasional breeze that gives
indication to the sharply cold wind that was buffered by the trees further
south.  The temperature continues to drop here and is decidedly bitter cold.
~
