#31686
the Norstar Taiga~
The many evergreen and pine trees that were present further south 
seem to dwindle in number, only a few surviving the climate here.
 Sounds of life have dwindled here to an almost eerie silence, except 
the occasional caw of a bird. A few mosses seem to thrive in this area,
 anchoring to areas where moisture is present. A thin grass has present 
in some places where it has the opportunity to utilize the patches on 
sunlight from above.
~
